Seoul in 1988, finished with 7,044 points - her best mark since a
world-record performance of 7,291 points at the 1988 Olympics.
Irina Belova of the Unified Team won silver with 6,845 points and Sabine
Braun of Germany captured bronze with 6,649.
The only other American woman to win back-to-back Olympic titles is Wyomia
Tyus, who triumphed in the 100m in 1964 and 1968.
