<TEXT>
A Rome magistrate has dropped an investigation of two former senior
officials of BNL, the Italian bank whose Atlanta branch granted Dollars
2.8bn (Pounds 1.46bn) of unauthorised loans to Iraq, AP reports from Rome.
Judge Vittorio De Cesare ruled that no irregularities had been committed by
