<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SPICES Prices of black and white pepper continued to ease this week, reports
Man Producten, as falling demand and accumulating selling pressure from some
producing countries resulted in a softer undertone. Prospects that prices
will soon recover seem poor. Big producers like Indonesia (white pepper) and
Brazil ( black pepper) will soon be coming to the market with their new crop
and though production is expected to be lower than in previous years on a
very good supply can still be counted on. Muntok white pepper is available
at Dollars 1,125 a tonne, cif, and black fair average quality at Dollars 825
a tonne, cif, prompt shipment from origin.
</TEXT>
