<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 92 / International Company News: Credit Suisse in talks to buy
Baden bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CREDIT SUISSE, Switzerland's third-largest bank, is in talks to buy
Gewerbebank Baden, the leading bank in the Baden region with assets of
SFr1.66bn (Dollars 1.21bn) at the end of June.
The talks are with BBC Brown Boveri, the Swiss partner in the ABB Asea Brown
Boveri engineering group, which holds a 38 per cent voting stake in the
bank. Winterthur Insurance, which holds 13 per cent of the votes, is also
co-operating.
Mr Leo Menz, senior vice-president, finance, of BBC, said the shares would
be sold at slightly above market prices, and that minority shareholders
would be offered identical terms in a public offer.
Gewerbebank Baden's bearer shares last traded at SFr760 earlier this week
and its registered shares at SFr255, valuing the bank at SFr123.8m.
The sale is part of BBC's policy to sell off participations in businesses
other than ABB. Following the sale of the bank, ABB would account for 99 per
cent of BBC's interests.
</TEXT>
