<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 92 / Explosions cause heavy casualties in Sarajevo
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SARAJEVO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A chain of explosions sowed terror and caused heavy casualties in central
Sarajevo yesterday in an attempt by rebel Serbs to force Bosnia's Moslem
leaders into peace negotiations, Reuter reports from Sarajevo. People fled
to safety as mortars fell on streets outside the presidency building,
parliament and city-centre shops in the worst daylight attacks for several
weeks in the Bosnian capital.
The fighting forced UN peacekeepers to close Sarajevo airport to relief
flights for the besieged city's 380,000 inhabitants and caused a visible
change of mood. The attack closed the airport just as General Lewis
MacKenzie, the outgoing commander of UN peacekeeping forces in Sarajevo, was
about to take off, Croatian radio said.
</TEXT>
