FT  31 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Dunkeld returns to profits of Pounds 0.6m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dunkeld Group, the clothing manufacturer formerly Aitch Holdings, returned
to profits in the six months to May 31. However, expected second half
losses, due to trading patterns, should reduce this for the year.
The new management said the turnround was achieved by a large reduction in
costs and substantially higher profits by subsidiaries. Under its
reorganisation 10 offshoots were closed or sold.
Pre-tax profits were Pounds 626,000, compared with losses of Pounds 995,000
and losses of Pounds 7.32m for the year to November 30, which included
exceptional costs of Pounds 2.86m. Turnover fell from Pounds 18.7m to Pounds
12m. Earnings per share came out at 0.9p (losses of 1.8p).
