FT  31 JUL 92 / UK Company News: LOFS announces change of domicile
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London &amp; Overseas Freighters, the tanker company controlled by the
Kulukundis family, is to be re-established under the same name in Bermuda,
but will keep its London listing.
The intention is to eliminate the tax disadvantages to international
investors of investing in a UK-resident company.
The move will be accompanied by the expansion of LOFS through the
acquisition of Scoresby, another Kulukundis company.
Scoresby was previously owned jointly by LOFS and Iroquois Shipping, another
Kulukundis family company. The acquisition will be achieved through the
issue of Pounds 7.4m worth of LOFS' shares to Iroquois.
