<TEXT>
Mary Thomson squandered her chance of an Olympic medal in spectacular
fashion, demolishing five fences in the decisive show-jumping phase of the
three-day event to slump to ninth overall. Team-mate Karen Dixon removed
only one rail to finish fifth.
