FT  31 JUL 92 / Property sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEPC, the UK's second-largest property company, has sold an office building
in Croydon, south London, to Rotch Property Group, a private company, for
about Pounds 45m.
The 442,500 sq ft building is let to the Department of the Environment. MEPC
said it had sold the building, called Apollo and Lunar House, because of its
limited prospects for rental growth.
