FT  31 JUL 92 / Move to shorten fraud trials
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT RICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT is to publish a consultation paper in the autumn on reducing
the length of trials for serious fraud, Robert Rice writes.
The consultation exercise follows a study by a working party set up after
the collapse of the second Guinness trial in February. The study's aim was
to identify changes in practice and procedure that would reduce the length
of such trials.
