FT  31 JUL 92 / Expulsions of Haitians can go on for now
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUREK MARTIN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE BUSH administration yesterday asked the Supreme Court initially to block
and then to reverse a lower court ruling that, on Wednesday, had overturned
its policy of forcibly returning home Haitian boat people, Jurek Martin
reports from Washington.
The Supreme Court gave lawyers representing the Haitians 24 hours to
respond. Also, an appeal court in New York delayed for 48 hours
implementation of its order to the Coast Guard to stop intercepting Haitians
on the high seas, pending a Supreme Court judgment. The Justice Department
said the appeal court decision 'will encourage another massive surge in
migration from Haiti.'
